        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 4:54PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kemper, or 8 miles east of Dillon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fairmont, Fair Bluff, Lake View, Boardman, Fork, Kemper, Barnesville,
Marietta, Proctorville, and Orrum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
